w but rarely see affirmed: that the lives they lead inside their own self-contained bodies; the skills they attain through their own concentration and rigor, and the unique phase in their lives during which they may explore boys and eroticism at their own pace - these are magical. And they constitute the entrance point to a life cycle of a sexuality that should be held sacred.', 14555, 0), (317250, 'It angered him that his sexuality was an issue at all. As far as he was concerned, who he decided to sleep with was his business alone.', 416, 0);
